cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM 

This paper deals with analyzing human motion in videos, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and computer graphics (cs.GR). The use of deep neural networks to extract a high-level latent motion representation suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the potential applications of the method in performance cloning, video-driven cartoons, and motion retrieval suggest a connection to multimedia (cs.MM).
